                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Mediocre</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red (strong red)</seg>
                        Scribe: Walda Tǝnśāʾe. The scribe’s
                        name, Walda Tǝnśāʾe, is written in the supplication formula on <locus target="#161vb">161vb</locus>.
 The same scribe wrote Ms.
                           KY-014.<date>Mid-20th century.</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; a few lines in the incipit page,
                           alternating with black lines; two initial lines of each section of the
                           text; elements of punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals; some
                           words such as ʾǝññanǝm (fol. 23vb), kä-zzih ba-ḫwala (fols. 39ra, 71rb),
                           ʾandǝm (e.g., fols. 50rb, 52rb, 53rb), qadāmihu qal (fol. 73ra),
                           dagmäññam (fol. 99rb), salām (e.g., fols. 162ra, 164rb, 165va),
                           etc.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
